1
00:00:00,380 --> 00:00:04,630
[Disclaimer: This series is entirely fictional
and solely for entertainment purposes

2
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:08,810
with no association or reference
to any individuals, places, or events;

3
00:00:08,850 --> 00:00:12,750
there may be inappropriate behaviors
and vulgarity based on the character's persona;

4
00:00:12,840 --> 00:00:15,000
viewer discretion is advised]

5
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:18,670
What do I do
if I want my fortune read by Master Ritt?

6
00:00:18,820 --> 00:00:20,810
I can smell chaos ensuing.

7
00:00:22,220 --> 00:00:23,080
The real one

8
00:00:23,520 --> 00:00:25,400
has come back to claim what's his.

9
00:00:27,070 --> 00:00:29,080
You're scared
to meet his real sweetheart?

10
00:00:29,120 --> 00:00:30,690
If they eventually meet...

11
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:32,700
Oh! Hey, I have to go.

12
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:34,980
If we weren't sweethearts,

13
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:38,200
it would've been hard
to approach you, huh?

14
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:41,570
Are you Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master?

15
00:00:41,820 --> 00:00:43,700
Do you mind taking another customer?

16
00:01:10,610 --> 00:01:12,370
You need to move on.

17
00:01:12,570 --> 00:01:14,240
He'll never get back to you again.

18
00:01:16,950 --> 00:01:19,039
Master Ritt's prophecy

19
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:21,370
can completely change someone's life.

20
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:26,300
Thank you so much.

21
00:01:42,220 --> 00:01:44,450
Is there any conflict of interest

22
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:46,880
behind your last prophecy?

23
00:01:47,759 --> 00:01:49,180
Pure...

24
00:01:49,870 --> 00:01:52,430
It'll make him understand his own feelings

25
00:01:52,570 --> 00:01:54,430
more than knowing his future, won't it?

26
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:56,360
Ritt,

27
00:01:56,570 --> 00:01:58,259
you've already thought about it, right?

28
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:01,680
Sometimes,

29
00:02:01,990 --> 00:02:05,510
the duty of a fortune teller
may not only be telling the truth,

30
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:07,990
but also helping the listener

31
00:02:08,190 --> 00:02:09,340
move on.

32
00:02:09,630 --> 00:02:11,870
Last time, he impersonated
Itthi's sweetheart.

33
00:02:12,180 --> 00:02:13,770
When his real sweetheart came,

34
00:02:14,110 --> 00:02:17,910
someone here now wants
that imagination to become reality.

35
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:32,990
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

36
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:37,079
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

37
00:02:37,110 --> 00:02:39,360
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

38
00:02:39,380 --> 00:02:45,560
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

39
00:02:45,590 --> 00:02:49,950
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

40
00:02:49,980 --> 00:02:53,360
♫Slightly out of line,♫

41
00:02:54,220 --> 00:02:57,910
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

42
00:02:57,940 --> 00:03:02,250
♫Try answering (if) your world
will cross with mine♫

43
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:06,330
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

44
00:03:06,350 --> 00:03:11,870
♫And I believe our love has power♫

45
00:03:11,890 --> 00:03:15,690
♫I believe the love of us♫

46
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:25,100
♫Will realign the stars back to the line
where they should be♫

47
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:46,050
[Master Ritt, are you home yet?
Are you drunk?]

48
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:59,100
[I'm going to sleep; good night.]

49
00:04:02,050 --> 00:04:07,570
[That's a short answer.
What's wrong? Are you exhausted?]

50
00:04:36,340 --> 00:04:38,090
Why did you wake up so late?

51
00:04:38,970 --> 00:04:40,540
Are you hungry?

52
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:43,310
I'm about to order dim sum by phone.
Do you want some?

53
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:45,220
Sounds good.

54
00:04:45,470 --> 00:04:47,620
Has the agency called you yet?

55
00:04:49,030 --> 00:04:51,470
Actually, Junhae has been asking

56
00:04:51,510 --> 00:04:53,400
if I've gotten better.

57
00:04:53,420 --> 00:04:55,620
That means they're still
interested in you.

58
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:58,060
I think so.

59
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,690
I think when your legs get better,

60
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,660
you should return to serious practice.

61
00:05:03,850 --> 00:05:06,710
You can use the old studio.
I'll make a reservation for you.

62
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:10,910
For your singing,
should we have Kim help train you?

63
00:05:12,070 --> 00:05:13,210
It's up to you, Mom.

64
00:05:14,210 --> 00:05:16,090
How can it be up to me?

65
00:05:16,210 --> 00:05:18,210
It's your life and your future.

66
00:05:19,090 --> 00:05:21,960
Well...whatever you say.

67
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:38,970
[No need to hurry;
just so you know, someone's waiting]

68
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:45,680
[Where are you?]

69
00:05:46,070 --> 00:05:49,460
[Look down at your left chest]

70
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:55,020
[I'm looking, what's in there?]

71
00:05:55,440 --> 00:06:00,030
[It's me in there;
do you have me in your heart?]

72
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:04,930
[Such a flirt,
where are you though?]

73
00:06:05,260 --> 00:06:08,840
[Waiting for you in front of the condo,
wanna see your face]

74
00:06:19,550 --> 00:06:21,400
Why didn't you let me know you'd come?

75
00:06:21,990 --> 00:06:23,820
How did you know I'm here?

76
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,560
I have a sixth sense.

77
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:28,530
Do you want to go anywhere today?

78
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:30,580
I'm so free that I can be with you all day.

79
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:32,740
I just sent my work last night.

80
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,430
I'm waiting for the comment.

81
00:06:34,450 --> 00:06:36,520
Which means...you're free.

82
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:40,220
I want to take you to one place.

83
00:06:46,570 --> 00:06:47,760
Be careful.

84
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:04,960
Hello.

85
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:08,050
Grandpa, Grandma, this is Ritt,

86
00:07:08,290 --> 00:07:09,290
my friend.

87
00:07:09,450 --> 00:07:12,200
Friend or boyfriend? Be honest.

88
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:17,790
Eat a lot so you grow faster.

89
00:07:17,820 --> 00:07:18,860
- Thank you very much.
- Grandpa.

90
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:20,340
Thank you.

91
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:24,820
They won't grow anymore.
They're fully grown already.

92
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:27,610
You came at the right time.

93
00:07:27,730 --> 00:07:30,020
We rarely get to have lunch together.

94
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:31,780
Come here more often, okay?

95
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,130
I love this.

96
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:36,490
So, are you Itthi's friend
at the university?

97
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:39,420
Why have I never seen you before?

98
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:41,920
He is my friend from high school, Grandma.

99
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:43,340
- Oh, I see.
- Oh.

100
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:45,970
What is your name again?
I couldn't clearly hear that.

101
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,240
My name is Ritt.

102
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:48,730
Ritt!

103
00:07:49,690 --> 00:07:51,730
Hey! Itthi's name is Itthi.

104
00:07:51,770 --> 00:07:52,770
Ritt. Itthi-Ritt.

105
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,600
Your names have a nice meaning together.

106
00:07:54,620 --> 00:07:56,100
That's destiny.

107
00:07:56,230 --> 00:07:57,960
Grandpa is right.

108
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,990
The name can tell your fortune.

109
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,440
Just like it's written in the stars.

110
00:08:07,210 --> 00:08:08,560
Well, have you graduated yet?

111
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:11,170
Not yet. I've been studying Architecture
for five years.

112
00:08:11,180 --> 00:08:12,700
This is my last year.

113
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:16,370
Ritt's project is also about beliefs,

114
00:08:16,410 --> 00:08:19,300
feng shui, and the energy
of house design materials.

115
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:21,500
Oh, that's perfect.

116
00:08:21,550 --> 00:08:25,150
Our company has all sorts
of seers, teachers, and feng shui masters.

117
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:28,010
- They are all great.
- And famous, too.

118
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:30,900
You can learn a lot from them.

119
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,940
Ritt is also a fortune teller.

120
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,820
- Really?
- A very famous one.

121
00:08:35,059 --> 00:08:36,570
People are lining up for him.

122
00:08:37,039 --> 00:08:39,100
What field are you in?

123
00:08:39,650 --> 00:08:41,190
Oh, he uses runestones.

124
00:08:41,289 --> 00:08:43,450
It's an ancient practice of the Vikings.

125
00:08:43,669 --> 00:08:45,090
Did the Vikings read fortunes?

126
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:47,110
Didn't they just sail boats
and wear horned helmets?

127
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,020
When you're free, give us a psychic reading.

128
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:52,110
- That's interesting.
- Alright?

129
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:53,910
Yes, sure.

130
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:56,420
By the way,
are you going anywhere this afternoon?

131
00:08:56,460 --> 00:09:00,510
If you're not in a rush, please wait
to meet our three feng shui masters.

132
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:03,870
- They may tell you something useful.
- Yeah.

133
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,290
Is that good?

134
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:09,980
Yeah, good.
Maybe it'll be useful for my project.

135
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:12,840
Mmm... Let's eat.

136
00:09:13,610 --> 00:09:15,570
Can you handle it?

137
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:43,570
This house is going to be chaotic.

138
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:52,190
The calamity is creeping in here.

139
00:09:53,290 --> 00:09:57,170
You're having bad luck.

140
00:09:57,620 --> 00:09:59,110
What are you doing?

141
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:03,870
Why don't you greet us
before foretelling our fates, huh?

142
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:07,280
Fate never tells us in advance.

143
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:11,050
Because the fate is sealed.

144
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:14,930
Do whatever you can, as soon as possible.

145
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:42,570
Cold in hands,
but warm in heart.

146
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:46,670
A star from the past
still shines on your future.

147
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:54,210
A swan-like forehead.

148
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:56,040
A falcon-like nose.

149
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:58,350
A dragon fruit. Oh!

150
00:10:58,830 --> 00:11:00,240
Dragon-like cheeks.

151
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:09,160
The north wind will blow on the subject.

152
00:11:09,390 --> 00:11:14,230
The brave mind is the great mind.

153
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:21,280
All the feng shui masters,
what do you mean by all that?

154
00:11:22,380 --> 00:11:23,640
Overall,

155
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,420
it means...

156
00:11:30,620 --> 00:11:32,060
Good!

157
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:34,030
So good!

158
00:11:34,930 --> 00:11:37,810
But you made it sound bad.

159
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:40,660
You!

160
00:11:42,310 --> 00:11:44,270
Why? What's going on with Itthi?

161
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:50,130
You said that
you don't believe in destiny.

162
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:53,700
But you know full well that it's not good.

163
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:56,050
It's not a major misfortune,

164
00:11:56,230 --> 00:12:00,240
but your heart makes it worse.

165
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:03,690
Bad wind

166
00:12:03,810 --> 00:12:06,200
blew right at you,

167
00:12:06,630 --> 00:12:09,740
so your star direction was changed.

168
00:12:10,140 --> 00:12:11,140
You don't believe that, right?

169
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:14,920
Within three days,

170
00:12:15,220 --> 00:12:19,100
there will be a little mishap to warn you.

171
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,300
But if it gets worse,

172
00:12:23,470 --> 00:12:26,400
we'll come back.

173
00:12:30,220 --> 00:12:32,090
It's not because of me, right?

174
00:12:32,570 --> 00:12:33,570
No!

175
00:12:34,390 --> 00:12:36,430
You're the lucky one.

176
00:12:36,650 --> 00:12:38,280
You have a strong destiny.

177
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:41,220
Lucky in having patrons.

178
00:12:41,680 --> 00:12:46,710
Your fate will support people besides you.

179
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:50,740
The sky always opens up for you.

180
00:12:51,690 --> 00:12:53,080
Hey, Itthi.

181
00:12:53,540 --> 00:12:57,440
If you go anywhere these days,
you'd better watch yourself.

182
00:12:57,840 --> 00:13:01,380
You should check carefully
before you walk.

183
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,450
But it's not fatal, right?

184
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,100
Not fatal.

185
00:13:07,510 --> 00:13:10,780
But if it isn't fixed soon,

186
00:13:11,870 --> 00:13:15,390
something fatal could happen.

187
00:13:15,870 --> 00:13:17,410
Aiya...

188
00:13:26,970 --> 00:13:29,620
How are our sales, my dear sister?

189
00:13:30,020 --> 00:13:31,620
Hot and cold.

190
00:13:31,690 --> 00:13:34,080
They're fluctuating, up and down.

191
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:35,540
Let me have a look.

192
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:40,980
Obviously,

193
00:13:41,260 --> 00:13:42,340
the sales increase because of Ritt.

194
00:13:46,060 --> 00:13:48,320
Yeah, you're right.

195
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:52,330
Well...should we ask him
to come here more often?

196
00:13:54,820 --> 00:13:57,490
Nowadays, I almost have to beg him

197
00:13:57,510 --> 00:13:59,510
to come here every time.

198
00:14:10,090 --> 00:14:12,380
Hey! Pure.

199
00:14:12,610 --> 00:14:14,460
I think I have a good idea.

200
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:17,230
Now that

201
00:14:17,340 --> 00:14:21,130
our shop is basically famous
thanks to Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master,

202
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:25,670
we should find
some more ways to boost sales.

203
00:14:25,730 --> 00:14:29,620
For example,
whenever Master Ritt comes to the shop,

204
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:31,680
we should set a rule that

205
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:35,690
the first table to reach a total of 1,000 baht

206
00:14:35,770 --> 00:14:38,790
gets priority for fortune reading.

207
00:14:39,110 --> 00:14:43,470
And...anyone with the highest monthly total,

208
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:45,790
like the top five spenders,

209
00:14:45,860 --> 00:14:47,970
will get a psychic reading reservation
for next month.

210
00:14:48,020 --> 00:14:49,260
Is that good?

211
00:14:49,650 --> 00:14:52,360
That means whenever Ritt comes to the shop,

212
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:55,680
the sales will increase since customers
need to compete for the highest sales.

213
00:14:56,690 --> 00:14:58,730
But what about the days
when Ritt doesn't come?

214
00:14:58,820 --> 00:15:00,720
Well...we should find the second Ritt

215
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:02,710
by covering, copying, cloning,

216
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:03,830
or should we find someone
who looks like him?

217
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:04,650
It's you.

218
00:15:05,090 --> 00:15:06,740
Go get dressed like Ritt.

219
00:15:06,810 --> 00:15:08,740
You'd better do it yourself, Pure.

220
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:12,100
Oh, hey.

221
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:13,840
Can you tell fortunes?

222
00:15:15,420 --> 00:15:16,620
No, I can't.

223
00:15:16,980 --> 00:15:19,170
So, can Ritt really do that?

224
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:21,790
Well...

225
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:22,960
That's it.

226
00:15:23,210 --> 00:15:24,480
Ritt can do it.

227
00:15:24,510 --> 00:15:27,020
So why can't you,
my beloved sister, do it?

228
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:29,970
It's not that hard.
I'll give you three days. Is it enough?

229
00:15:30,010 --> 00:15:31,900
You're joking, Pure.

230
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,550
Focus on our sales,

231
00:15:34,730 --> 00:15:36,630
so we can do anything,

232
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:38,300
my dear sister.

233
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:40,890
Our sales. Our sales.

234
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:45,610
You can do it.

235
00:15:51,560 --> 00:15:52,400
Hey!

236
00:15:53,630 --> 00:15:55,910
I think I'll be lucky tonight.

237
00:16:00,780 --> 00:16:03,080
This is the sign of luck,

238
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:05,020
having someone cute wipe it for me.

239
00:16:10,790 --> 00:16:12,460
You stole a kiss!

240
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:16,230
Will you file a complaint?

241
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:18,400
If so, I'll report back

242
00:16:18,430 --> 00:16:20,720
that my heart was stolen by someone, too.

243
00:16:32,730 --> 00:16:34,540
Hey, brother!
My brakes aren't working!

244
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:36,460
Step aside. Watch out, bro!

245
00:16:48,850 --> 00:16:51,010
I'm sorry. Are you alright, bro?

246
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,450
It's okay, bro.

247
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:57,040
I'm so sorry.
I couldn't really use the brakes.

248
00:17:03,180 --> 00:17:04,359
Are you okay?

249
00:17:04,660 --> 00:17:06,040
Things that feng shui masters told...

250
00:17:09,030 --> 00:17:11,130
Accidents can occur anytime.

251
00:17:11,630 --> 00:17:12,560
We just have to be careful.

252
00:17:18,710 --> 00:17:19,920
There you go.

253
00:17:24,140 --> 00:17:25,140
Sorry.

254
00:17:25,410 --> 00:17:26,560
Are you okay?

255
00:17:28,510 --> 00:17:30,610
- I'm okay.
- I'm really sorry.

256
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:35,400
Are you hurt?

257
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:36,760
Can you blow the pain away?

258
00:17:37,210 --> 00:17:38,820
Still kidding, huh?

259
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:41,120
This happens back to back.

260
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:43,480
If so, you have to take good care of me.

261
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:57,350
Oh.

262
00:17:57,890 --> 00:18:00,080
What brought my best friend here?

263
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:02,740
- Fine, I can go back now.
- Hey, I'm kidding.

264
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:04,370
Come on, let's have a seat.

265
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:05,520
What would you like to drink?

266
00:18:05,620 --> 00:18:07,600
What about you, Itthi?
Will you drink today?

267
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:08,720
I'll have just a mocktail.

268
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:12,930
How long is the queue tonight?

269
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:15,110
What queue are you talking about?

270
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:16,670
You didn't tell me you would come,

271
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:17,900
so how on earth would the customers know?

272
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:19,240
But you've come at the right time.

273
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:20,900
I have something to talk to you about.

274
00:18:21,110 --> 00:18:23,190
It's a great deal from our bar.

275
00:18:24,310 --> 00:18:26,850
Can I talk to Ritt just a moment?

276
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:29,490
Let Ploy take care of you first, Itthi.

277
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:37,410
Here is the thing, buddy.

278
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:39,370
My genius sister

279
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:42,560
came up with a bright idea
to boost our sales:

280
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:46,520
the table that reaches 1,000 in sales first

281
00:18:46,820 --> 00:18:49,630
will get a chance to have their fortune read
by Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master.

282
00:18:49,930 --> 00:18:52,730
And monthly totals will be accumulated.

283
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:55,150
The top five spenders

284
00:18:55,380 --> 00:18:57,720
will get to have their fortune read
by Master Ritt next month.

285
00:18:58,040 --> 00:19:00,920
How's it? It's a good idea, isn't it?

286
00:19:03,540 --> 00:19:04,830
I think...

287
00:19:09,170 --> 00:19:10,610
I'm going to quit.

288
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:11,960
What?

289
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:13,910
Why?

290
00:19:15,930 --> 00:19:16,790
Well...

291
00:19:16,850 --> 00:19:19,530
You know I'm not a real fortune teller.

292
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:21,410
Also,

293
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:24,400
I think this is going too far.

294
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:29,950
Is this because you got
a reading for Pitcha,

295
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,580
the real sweetheart of Itthi?

296
00:19:35,690 --> 00:19:36,690
Well, yes.

297
00:19:37,990 --> 00:19:39,380
Before this,

298
00:19:39,410 --> 00:19:41,990
my prophecies were neither right nor wrong.

299
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:45,380
They were words that

300
00:19:45,460 --> 00:19:48,230
could be interpreted
in a way that is good for the customers.

301
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:51,030
But for Pitcha that night...

302
00:19:51,420 --> 00:19:52,500
I lied to him,

303
00:19:53,410 --> 00:19:54,980
which I thought was not okay.

304
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:59,410
And now, I think

305
00:19:59,820 --> 00:20:01,810
I'll try to tell Itthi the truth

306
00:20:02,110 --> 00:20:03,930
about my impersonation.

307
00:20:05,340 --> 00:20:06,340
Well...

308
00:20:06,690 --> 00:20:08,200
I understand you, buddy.

309
00:20:08,930 --> 00:20:12,480
But can you please help me a little longer?

310
00:20:12,650 --> 00:20:17,370
Now, I'm trying to convince Ployplern
to act on your behalf.

311
00:20:20,550 --> 00:20:21,940
Anyway, for now,

312
00:20:22,070 --> 00:20:24,440
can you come to my bar

313
00:20:25,430 --> 00:20:27,620
just twice a week?

314
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:37,540
Once a week.

315
00:20:37,830 --> 00:20:38,620
Sure, buddy.

316
00:20:38,780 --> 00:20:41,200
And I'll be the one who juggles,

317
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:43,190
so you don't meet Pitcha here.

318
00:20:44,630 --> 00:20:45,750
Does he still come here?

319
00:20:45,990 --> 00:20:47,630
He's almost a regular customer.

320
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,040
But I think...

321
00:20:50,990 --> 00:20:53,290
he looks lonely.

322
00:20:54,170 --> 00:20:55,920
He looks like he has no friends.

323
00:20:56,590 --> 00:21:00,850
On the outside,
he's like a calm and strong person,

324
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:03,850
but I think

325
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:07,080
he hides a lot of things inside.

326
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:10,880
You're weird.

327
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:14,700
How's it weird?

328
00:21:15,540 --> 00:21:16,720
Wait a minute.

329
00:21:19,420 --> 00:21:22,250
Don't tell me that...

330
00:21:22,380 --> 00:21:23,800
You...

331
00:21:23,830 --> 00:21:26,170
Yeah, maybe.

332
00:21:27,550 --> 00:21:29,530
Anyway, I'm asking you

333
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:31,540
to come here once a week, okay?

334
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:34,640
Until Ployplern can
professionally act for you.

335
00:21:36,690 --> 00:21:39,200
Okay! Deal.

336
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:45,990
Your face is turning red, Itthi.

337
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:47,470
Are you drunk from a cocktail?

338
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:50,300
Ployplern's recipe is pretty strong.

339
00:21:50,460 --> 00:21:51,800
She's talented.

340
00:21:51,930 --> 00:21:54,310
She can do anything, right?

341
00:21:54,910 --> 00:21:56,290
Of course, yes.

342
00:22:01,020 --> 00:22:02,020
Do you want more?

343
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,430
Pitcha is here.

344
00:22:04,210 --> 00:22:05,430
There are various recipes.

345
00:22:06,550 --> 00:22:08,010
Oh, hey. Something fell down.

346
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:09,390
- How can you be here?
- Can you help me pick that up?

347
00:22:09,430 --> 00:22:11,460
Can you go outside with me?

348
00:22:11,490 --> 00:22:13,690
- Let's go.
- What happened?

349
00:22:14,510 --> 00:22:15,870
What are you looking for?

350
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:22,250
Why are you bringing me outside?

351
00:22:22,940 --> 00:22:24,560
- Is something wrong?
- Uh...

352
00:22:25,660 --> 00:22:27,370
Can you go buy something with me?

353
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:29,240
Something?

354
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:30,470
What is it?

355
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:32,970
Ice.

356
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:34,890
Ployplern told me the ice has run out.

357
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:36,390
So I have to go buy it myself.

358
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:37,920
Please, come on.

359
00:22:37,930 --> 00:22:38,780
Let's go buy some ice together.

360
00:22:44,290 --> 00:22:46,050
I think it already disappeared.

361
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:47,130
Never mind.

362
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:55,220
I'm hungry. Are you hungry?

363
00:22:55,590 --> 00:22:57,330
Ritt, you can take Itthi to the kitchen,

364
00:22:57,340 --> 00:22:59,460
so you can cook what you want to eat.

365
00:22:59,780 --> 00:23:00,880
- Come on, go.
- Uh-huh.

366
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:05,500
- Make yourself at home.
- Okay.

367
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:06,900
Yes, Chef.

368
00:23:12,990 --> 00:23:14,190
Is there anything you want to eat?

369
00:23:14,350 --> 00:23:15,680
Well...

370
00:23:16,350 --> 00:23:18,710
An omelet, a fried egg, and scrambled eggs,

371
00:23:18,740 --> 00:23:20,970
Thai-style scrambled eggs, and egg...

372
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:23,300
Isn't this a bit too much of an insult?

373
00:23:24,290 --> 00:23:27,300
Let this chef show you what he can do.

374
00:23:27,370 --> 00:23:28,740
You are my apprentice. Okay?

375
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:31,140
Okay, roger that.

376
00:24:02,190 --> 00:24:04,610
- It's starting to take shape.
- Does it smell good?

377
00:24:07,830 --> 00:24:09,180
Can I have some ice, please?

378
00:24:09,970 --> 00:24:10,970
Sir.

379
00:24:13,380 --> 00:24:14,750
Is there anyone here?

380
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:16,680
Sir.

381
00:24:17,660 --> 00:24:19,190
Let's get in there and get it done.

382
00:24:21,120 --> 00:24:22,120
I'll tell him later.

383
00:24:30,020 --> 00:24:31,590
Can you help me lift it?

384
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:43,030
Are you okay with this?

385
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:44,910
I'm okay.

386
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:48,470
- Hey.
- Hey.

387
00:24:49,740 --> 00:24:50,980
Hold on.

388
00:25:01,230 --> 00:25:03,070
We are stuck inside.

389
00:25:03,740 --> 00:25:04,740
Open the door, please.

390
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:05,980
Can anyone hear me?

391
00:25:08,010 --> 00:25:10,950
Just a second.
I'd better call the owner.

392
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:25,400
He isn't answering.

393
00:25:27,930 --> 00:25:29,080
Can you stand it?

394
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:32,500
Yes, I can.

395
00:25:32,910 --> 00:25:34,320
It's colder than when I was in Korea.

396
00:25:35,230 --> 00:25:36,390
Really?

397
00:25:36,930 --> 00:25:39,190
I'm not used to the cold.

398
00:25:39,810 --> 00:25:41,800
My shirt is also thin.

399
00:25:44,810 --> 00:25:46,150
What are you doing?

400
00:25:47,540 --> 00:25:49,950
- You'll freeze to death.
- Hey, I'm fine. Just put it on.

401
00:25:49,980 --> 00:25:51,500
- You'd better put it on.
- No, you should.

402
00:26:27,770 --> 00:26:29,640
This is pretty good, right?

403
00:26:31,860 --> 00:26:33,260
We are both warm.

404
00:26:44,090 --> 00:26:45,580
Oh, what are you doing here?

405
00:26:45,790 --> 00:26:47,060
You'll freeze to death.

406
00:26:47,090 --> 00:26:49,090
The door isn't even locked. Come out.

407
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:52,900
I came here to buy some ice.

408
00:26:54,190 --> 00:26:55,460
How many sacks would you like?

409
00:26:55,690 --> 00:26:57,080
Four sacks.

410
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:58,200
Wait a minute.

411
00:26:58,300 --> 00:26:59,280
Kob! Kob!

412
00:26:59,440 --> 00:27:01,440
Kob, get the customers some ice.

413
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:03,850
Oh, me again?

414
00:27:20,070 --> 00:27:21,180
Are you hurt?

415
00:27:22,730 --> 00:27:23,930
It burned a little.

416
00:27:24,260 --> 00:27:25,400
It's okay.

417
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:28,710
Just a little bit. I'll be fine.

418
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:32,350
But the point is, I broke their bowl.

419
00:27:33,480 --> 00:27:34,870
- Ouch!
- Oh!

420
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:36,280
Did you get cut?

421
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:38,250
Let me see.

422
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:41,990
Let's clean it with salt water first.

423
00:27:42,450 --> 00:27:43,600
Does it hurt?

424
00:27:44,890 --> 00:27:45,890
I think

425
00:27:46,780 --> 00:27:49,010
you should've been
a nurse instead of a chef.

426
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:54,250
Go clean it first. Let's go.

427
00:28:07,950 --> 00:28:09,210
Or maybe

428
00:28:09,260 --> 00:28:12,020
what feng shui masters
warned us is true.

429
00:28:14,750 --> 00:28:16,320
It happens back to back.

430
00:28:16,730 --> 00:28:17,870
What do you think?

431
00:28:20,180 --> 00:28:21,300
What happened to you, Itthi?

432
00:28:21,900 --> 00:28:23,430
I was cut by some shards.

433
00:28:23,730 --> 00:28:25,230
Does it hurt a lot?

434
00:28:25,500 --> 00:28:26,500
A little bit.

435
00:28:26,900 --> 00:28:27,990
I'm sorry, though.

436
00:28:28,890 --> 00:28:30,600
I broke your bowl.

437
00:28:31,250 --> 00:28:34,220
It's okay as long as you're safe.

438
00:28:35,830 --> 00:28:38,490
Well, we'd better go now.

439
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:41,840
Let's eat the instant noodles at home.
Okay?

440
00:28:44,980 --> 00:28:46,550
Can you still drive?

441
00:28:47,180 --> 00:28:48,880
Your hand is wrapped like that.

442
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:51,040
Another accident may occur again.

443
00:28:52,700 --> 00:28:54,070
Can you drive, though?

444
00:28:56,300 --> 00:28:57,280
A little bit.

445
00:28:57,490 --> 00:28:58,550
I have a driving license.

446
00:28:59,240 --> 00:29:00,200
But...

447
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:02,510
it's been a long time since I drove.

448
00:29:04,260 --> 00:29:05,590
So...

449
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:08,120
you'll probably play another role today.

450
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:10,500
From a fortune teller

451
00:29:10,830 --> 00:29:11,880
to a chef,

452
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:13,200
a nurse,

453
00:29:14,010 --> 00:29:15,410
and now a chauffeur.

454
00:29:17,770 --> 00:29:19,060
Are you brave enough to be my passenger?

455
00:29:20,270 --> 00:29:21,440
If you are,

456
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:25,210
I'll drive.

457
00:29:26,210 --> 00:29:27,210
No problem.

458
00:29:28,060 --> 00:29:29,790
I feel comfortable when I'm with you.

459
00:29:30,700 --> 00:29:31,850
I'm not afraid of anything.

460
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:41,680
Turn right... Go left. No, no.

461
00:29:41,770 --> 00:29:44,000
- Go right. Brake. Brake first.
- What the hell?!

462
00:29:44,060 --> 00:29:45,590
Brake. Hey, brake.

463
00:29:45,680 --> 00:29:47,430
Brake, brake, brake!

464
00:29:54,150 --> 00:29:55,130
Hey, wait.

465
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:01,120
Ploy,

466
00:30:01,450 --> 00:30:03,780
the ice is here.
Can I come in now?

467
00:30:05,430 --> 00:30:08,000
Okay. Safe. I'll come in now.

468
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:11,720
Hey, let's go.

469
00:30:15,100 --> 00:30:18,050
Since you've already helped this much,

470
00:30:18,340 --> 00:30:20,130
you might as well
help me bring them to the back.

471
00:30:21,050 --> 00:30:22,050
No problem.

472
00:30:22,750 --> 00:30:23,960
- Come on.
- Come on.

473
00:30:30,850 --> 00:30:32,080
It's pretty heavy, huh?

474
00:30:32,530 --> 00:30:33,820
It's easy for me.

475
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:39,480
Ending today with instant noodles.

476
00:30:40,540 --> 00:30:41,610
When I'm with you,

477
00:30:42,670 --> 00:30:43,800
everything is delicious.

478
00:30:44,040 --> 00:30:45,000
Stop.

479
00:30:45,340 --> 00:30:46,610
Let's eat while it's still hot.

480
00:30:47,630 --> 00:30:49,040
When we were in the car,

481
00:30:49,380 --> 00:30:51,320
you didn't stop complaining
about being hungry.

482
00:30:58,610 --> 00:30:59,920
It's difficult for me to eat.

483
00:31:01,170 --> 00:31:01,770
Feed me, please.

484
00:31:01,810 --> 00:31:02,950
Well,

485
00:31:04,050 --> 00:31:05,850
you're taking advantage of this, huh?

486
00:31:11,710 --> 00:31:12,840
Blow it for me.

487
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:23,850
Hey, Itthi.

488
00:31:24,010 --> 00:31:26,440
What are you quietly doing there?

489
00:31:27,480 --> 00:31:28,500
We're having a late dinner.

490
00:31:29,180 --> 00:31:30,550
- I see.
- Would you like to join us, Grandma?

491
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:32,320
No, I wouldn't.

492
00:31:36,530 --> 00:31:39,700
What's wrong with your hand?
Why is it bandaged like that?

493
00:31:42,090 --> 00:31:43,430
It's just a small wound.

494
00:31:45,930 --> 00:31:47,280
Oh, what about this?

495
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:50,240
What happened to your forehead?

496
00:31:51,900 --> 00:31:53,160
I bumped into a door.

497
00:31:53,210 --> 00:31:54,210
Bumped into the door?

498
00:31:56,660 --> 00:31:58,380
It's pretty strange

499
00:31:58,420 --> 00:32:00,900
since feng shui masters
warned you about that.

500
00:32:01,190 --> 00:32:05,110
Let's put it this way: I'll have them
give you a detailed reading tomorrow

501
00:32:05,140 --> 00:32:06,940
to see whether there is anything
you can fix.

502
00:32:08,420 --> 00:32:09,690
Be careful, though.

503
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,290
I'm going to bed now.

504
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:12,210
Yes, Grandma.

505
00:32:13,100 --> 00:32:13,870
Bye.

506
00:32:14,750 --> 00:32:16,610
- Good night, Grandma.
- Good night.

507
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:19,070
[We're open; come in!]

508
00:32:36,010 --> 00:32:37,550
Hey, thank you very much

509
00:32:38,030 --> 00:32:39,700
for helping me until the bar is closed.

510
00:32:41,250 --> 00:32:42,980
Can I have a meal for my wages?

511
00:32:43,510 --> 00:32:45,400
Well, wait a minute.

512
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:28,800
I'm sorry.

513
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:30,120
The kitchen is already closed.

514
00:33:30,490 --> 00:33:31,740
I don't want to reopen it.

515
00:33:32,700 --> 00:33:34,610
Let's eat some hot instant noodles instead.

516
00:33:34,650 --> 00:33:37,800
There are two eggs for you.

517
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:42,040
But it's the only cup left.
So let's share it, okay?

518
00:33:43,420 --> 00:33:44,170
Uh-huh.

519
00:33:44,930 --> 00:33:45,800
Thank you.

520
00:33:49,340 --> 00:33:50,340
Pretty hot.

521
00:33:55,300 --> 00:33:56,220
And...

522
00:33:57,140 --> 00:33:58,390
Doesn't coming here often

523
00:33:58,940 --> 00:33:59,940
bore you?

524
00:34:03,660 --> 00:34:07,100
Well, I don't usually go anywhere else.

525
00:34:12,159 --> 00:34:13,159
Why?

526
00:34:16,380 --> 00:34:17,870
I grew up in Korea.

527
00:34:18,940 --> 00:34:20,409
I was not very close to my friends there.

528
00:34:21,070 --> 00:34:23,080
And here... I also don't
have many friends.

529
00:34:30,020 --> 00:34:32,000
So...do you feel lonely?

530
00:34:35,100 --> 00:34:37,110
Why? Do I look lonely?

531
00:34:39,250 --> 00:34:40,710
Your eyes show it.

532
00:34:43,989 --> 00:34:45,040
What do they show?

533
00:34:48,650 --> 00:34:49,790
They show that you're like

534
00:34:50,500 --> 00:34:52,210
someone who's trying to be okay.

535
00:34:53,460 --> 00:34:56,510
But actually, you're not okay.

536
00:35:01,620 --> 00:35:02,810
For some people,

537
00:35:03,830 --> 00:35:07,400
their eyes are shining
when they're doing something they like.

538
00:35:09,190 --> 00:35:11,480
But...the glint in your eyes

539
00:35:12,530 --> 00:35:13,820
is like that of someone

540
00:35:14,110 --> 00:35:16,100
trying to find a way out
of the loneliness in their heart.

541
00:35:23,180 --> 00:35:24,180
Next time I come here,

542
00:35:24,860 --> 00:35:26,090
I'll wear sunglasses.

543
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,080
If you have something on your mind,

544
00:35:33,950 --> 00:35:35,240
you can say it to me.

545
00:35:36,170 --> 00:35:38,140
Even though I may not be able to help you much,

546
00:35:38,350 --> 00:35:40,400
